sbpro-card
    .card-header Adaptive Grayscale
    .card-body
        .border.border-lg.rounded
            .p-4.border-bottom
                .bg-white.p-3 .bg-white
                .bg-gray-100.p-3 .bg-gray-100
                .bg-gray-200.p-3 .bg-gray-200
                .bg-gray-300.p-3 .bg-gray-300
                .bg-gray-400.p-3 .bg-gray-400
                .bg-gray-500.text-white.p-3 .bg-gray-500
                .bg-gray-600.text-white.p-3 .bg-gray-600
                .bg-gray-700.text-white.p-3 .bg-gray-700
                .bg-gray-800.text-white.p-3 .bg-gray-800
                .bg-gray-900.text-white.p-3 .bg-gray-900
                .bg-black.text-white.p-3 .bg-black
            .bg-light.p-4.small
                p.
                    The adaptive grayscale is a custom feature in SB Admin Pro.
                    The grayscale is formed by setting a value to the <code>$grayscale-base-hue</code> variable in the <code>src/styles/sb-admin-pro/variables/_colors.scss</code> file.
                    The base hue, set to blue by default, is then blended with a true black and white grayscale to make a slightly tinted grayscale that is used throughout the theme.
                p.mb-0.
                    You can use the above utilty classes as background colors for your elements,
                    and you can modify the adaptive grayscale within the <code>src/styles/sb-admin-pro/variables/_colors.scss</code> file.
